The Fund consists of:
Moneys transferred from the Maryland Health Insurance Plan Fund;
Moneys collected from any assessment by the State Health Services Cost Review Commission on hospitals under § 19-214(d) of this article;
Any moneys made available from investment earnings; and
Any other moneys from any other source accepted for the benefit of the Fund.

The Fund may be used only for expenses associated with:
Expanding Medicaid eligibility for parents and caretaker relatives:
Who have a dependent child living with them; and
Whose annual household income is at or below 116% of the federal poverty guidelines;
Expanding Medicaid eligibility and benefits for individuals:
Who do not meet requirements, such as age, disability, or parent or caretaker relative of a dependent child, for a federal category of eligibility for Medicaid;
Whose annual household income is at or below 116% of the federal poverty guidelines; and
Who are not enrolled in the federal Medicare program, as enacted by Title XVIII of the Social Security Act;
Providing and administering health benefit plan premium subsidies under Title 15, Subtitle 12A of the Insurance Article; and
Supporting the provision of health care services in Prince George's County in accordance with subsection (i) of this section.

section.section:
The long-term, comprehensive solution under paragraph (2) of this subsection shall address issues related to health care needs in Prince George's County and the surrounding region, including:
The transfer to a new owner or operator of the facilities currently operated and the obligation to provide the health care services currently provided by Dimensions Healthcare System;
A plan for the assets currently held by Prince George's County related to the facilities currently operated by Dimensions Healthcare System;
A mechanism to provide a steady revenue stream to help support ongoing operations of the facilities currently operated by Dimensions Healthcare System and to retire the long-term bond indebtedness and satisfy the unfunded pension liability of Dimensions Healthcare System; and
A mechanism to assure equitable and sustainable funding from Prince George's County and the State.
